      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Former Husband Responds</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Carl Friedan letter denies that he was evern physically abusive to Betty Friedan, his ex-wife, as she charges in new memoir (May 11 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your interview with my ex-wife, Betty Friedan (''Beyond Mystique, a Frank Memoir,'' May 11), reflects her charges that I was physically abusive to her, charges that appear in her new book of memoirs.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your interview with my ex-wife, Betty Friedan (''Beyond Mystique, a Frank Memoir,'' May 11), reflects her charges that I was physically abusive to her, charges that appear in her new book of memoirs.</p>
        <p>The charges are blatantly untrue. Never in my life have I ever gratuitously struck anyone.</p>
        <p>CARL FRIEDAN  Sarasota, Fla.</p>
      </block>
